## Epic Lifecycle

### Creating an Epic

1. Administrator identifies a large-scale initiative
2. Create epic file with appropriate priority
3. Define clear goals and success criteria
4. Link to relevant architecture decisions (ADRs)
5. Break down into specific tasks for various roles

### During Development

- Track progress through subtasks in the dashboard
- Update status as work progresses (TODO ‚Üí UNDERWAY)
- Document decisions and adjustments in Notes section
- Keep Related Architecture section up to date

### Completing an Epic

1. Verify all success criteria are met
2. Ensure all subtasks are completed or closed
3. Update status to COMPLETE
4. Document outcomes and lessons learned
5. Reference epic in related commit messages and PRs


